37527c9c6930dd86d5d012e94d2e08d6a207d240 could add a comment here that we're deleting the unencrypted key. Or make the intention more readable:

```cpp
const auto db_key_plain_text = std::make_pair(DBKeys::HDKEY, xpub);
const auto db_key_encrypted = std::make_pair(DBKeys::HDCKEY, xpub);
if (!WriteIC(db_key_plain_text, std::make_pair(crypted_key, checksum), false)) {
    return false;
}
EraseIC(db_key_unencrypted);

```

I find it a worrying that no test caught the fact that we weren't deleting this in an earlier version of the PR (b88337daba). Can we introduce a test that looks for unencrypted key material e.g. by just checking _every_ record?

